AB  - Accurate carbon price forecasting can better allocate carbon emissions and thus ensure a balance between economic development and potential climate impacts. In this paper, we propose a new two-stage framework based on processes of decomposition and re-estimation to forecast prices across international carbon markets. We focus on the Emissions Trading System (ETS) in the EU, as well as the five main pilot schemes in China, spanning the period from May 2014 to January 2022. In this way, the raw carbon prices are first separated into multiple sub-factors and then reconstructed into factors of 'trend' and 'period' with the use of Singular Spectrum Analysis (SSA). Once the subsequences have been thus decomposed, we further apply six machine learning and deep learning methods, allowing the data to be assembled and thus facilitating the prediction of the final carbon price values. We find that from amongst these machine learning models, the Support vector regression (SSA-SVR) and Least squares support vector regression (SSA-LSSVR) stand out in terms of performance for the prediction of carbon prices in both the European ETS and equivalent models in China. Another interesting finding to come out of our experiments is that the sophisticated algorithms are far from being the best performing models in the prediction of carbon prices. Even after accounting for the impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic and other macro-economic variables, as well as the prices of other energy sources, our framework still works effectively.
AB  - 准确的碳价格预测可以更好地分配碳排放量，从而确保经济发展与潜在气候影响之间的平衡。 在本文中，我们提出了一个基于分解和再估计过程的两阶段新框架，用于预测国际碳市场的价格。 我们重点关注欧盟的排放交易体系（ETS）以及中国的五大试点计划，时间跨度为 2014 年 5 月至 2022 年 1 月。 通过这种方法，我们首先将原始碳价格分解为多个子因子，然后利用奇异频谱分析法（SSA）将其重构为 "趋势 "和 "时期 "因子。 在对子因子进行分解后，我们进一步应用六种机器学习和深度学习方法，对数据进行组合，从而促进对最终碳价格值的预测。 我们发现，在这些机器学习模型中，支持向量回归（SSA-SVR）和最小二乘支持向量回归（SSA-LSSVR）在预测欧洲排放交易计划和中国同等模型的碳价格方面表现突出。 实验的另一个有趣发现是，复杂算法远非预测碳价格的最佳模型。 即使考虑了 COVID-19 大流行病和其他宏观经济变量的影响，以及其他能源的价格，我们的框架仍然有效。
