AB  - Acrylic acid is a value-added chemical used in industry to produce diapers, coatings, paints, and adhesives, among many others. Due to its economic importance, there is currently a need for new and sustainable ways to synthesise it. Recently, the focus has been laid in the use of Escherichia coli to express the full bio-based pathway using 3-hydroxypropionate as an intermediary through three distinct pathways (glycerol, malonyl-CoA, and beta-alanine). Hence, the goals of this work were to use COPASI software to assess which of the three pathways has a higher potential for industrial-scale production, from either glucose or glycerol, and identify potential targets to improve the biosynthetic pathways yields. When compared to the available literature, the models developed during this work successfully predict the production of 3-hydroxypropionate, using glycerol as carbon source in the glycerol pathway, and using glucose as a carbon source in the malonyl-CoA and beta-alanine pathways. Finally, this work allowed to identify four potential over-expression targets (glycerol-3-phosphate dehydrogenase (G3pD), acetyl-CoA carboxylase (AccC), aspartate aminotransferase (AspAT), and aspartate carboxylase (AspC)) that should, theoretically, result in higher AA yields.
AB  - 丙烯酸是一种高附加值化学品，在工业中用于生产尿布、涂料、油漆和粘合剂等。 由于其经济重要性，目前需要新的、可持续的丙烯酸合成方法。 最近，研究重点是利用大肠杆菌，通过三种不同的途径（甘油、丙二酸丙二酯和β-丙氨酸），表达以 3-羟基丙酸酯为中间体的完整生物基途径。 因此，这项工作的目标是使用 COPASI 软件来评估这三种途径中哪一种更有可能以葡萄糖或甘油为原料进行工业规模生产，并确定提高生物合成途径产量的潜在目标。 与现有文献相比，这项工作中开发的模型成功预测了在甘油途径中使用甘油作为碳源以及在丙二酰-CoA 和 beta-丙氨酸途径中使用葡萄糖作为碳源生产 3-羟基丙酸酯的情况。 最后，这项工作确定了四个潜在的过度表达目标（甘油-3-磷酸脱氢酶（G3pD）、乙酰-CoA 羧化酶（AccC）、天冬氨酸氨基转移酶（AspAT）和天冬氨酸羧化酶（AspC）），这些目标理论上应可提高 AA 产量。
