AB  - The transport sector as a whole plays an important role in the economy of Bangladesh as its contribution to gross domestic product (GDP) stood at 10.98 percent in the fiscal year (FY) 2018-19 with a growth rate of 6.88 percent. However, this sector also accounted for 9.92 percent of the country's total greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions in 2020. This GHG emission is projected to grow by 116 percent by 2030, making decarbonization of transport an urgent priority by uptaking the electric vehicle (EV). Hence, the Government of Bangladesh is presently working towards issuing an EV policy to remove the barriers to accommodate this paradigm shift in the transportation sector. In order to develop an effective policy for scaling up EV uptake in Bangladesh, systematic and detailed forecasting needs to be carried out considering various influencing parameters. In this study, an EV outlook for Bangladesh from 2022 to 2040 has been formulated by applying the concepts of the additive linear programming mechanism. The predictive modelling includes linear growth of ICE vehicles, EV price reduction, and inclusion of carbon tax on ICE cars as contributing factors in this paper. It has been estimated that, with the inclusion of a 40% carbon tax, the forecasted number of EVs would reach around 3,000,000 in the year 2040. The outlook has led to a comparative financial analysis between ICE vehicles and EVs through the establishment of financial modelling. The genetic algorithm optimizes total tax incidence (TTI) that limits the payback period, and hence, reduces the price gaps between EVs and ICE vehicles. Based on the findings of the study, a number of policies are recommended on fiscal and financial incentives to pave the way for increased uptake of EVs in Bangladesh.
AB  - 运输部门作为一个整体在孟加拉国经济中发挥着重要作用，在 2018-19 财年，其对国内生产总值（GDP）的贡献率为 10.98%，增长率为 6.88%。然而，到 2020 年，该部门的温室气体（GHG）排放量也占全国总排放量的 9.92%。预计到 2030 年，温室气体排放量将增长 116%，因此，通过推广电动汽车（EV）来实现交通脱碳已成为当务之急。因此，孟加拉国政府目前正在努力出台一项电动汽车政策，以消除障碍，适应交通部门的这一模式转变。为了制定有效的政策，扩大电动汽车在孟加拉国的使用范围，需要考虑各种影响参数，进行系统而详细的预测。在本研究中，通过应用加法线性规划机制的概念，制定了孟加拉国 2022 年至 2040 年的电动汽车前景。预测模型包括内燃机汽车的线性增长、电动汽车价格下降，以及将内燃机汽车碳税作为本文的促成因素。据估计，如果征收 40% 的碳税，到 2040 年，电动汽车的预测数量将达到约 3,000,000 辆。通过建立财务模型，本文对内燃机汽车和电动汽车的财务状况进行了比较分析。遗传算法优化了限制投资回收期的总税收（TTI），从而缩小了电动汽车和内燃机汽车之间的价格差距。根据研究结果，建议采取一系列财政和金融激励政策，为提高孟加拉国电动汽车的使用率铺平道路。
