AB  - Several countries have formulated carbon-neutral plans in dealing with global warming, which have also derived various carbon trading markets. All parties involved in carbon trading aim to obtain the maximum benefit from it, and this requires participants to accurately judge the carbon trading price. This study then proposes a two-stage heterogeneous ensemble method for predicting carbon trading prices. To accurately capture the characteristics of the time series data, we extracted four feature sets based on the lag length, moving average, variational mode decomposition, and empirical mode decomposition methods. Subsequently, four algorithms, linear regression, neural network, random forest, and XGBoost, constructed the first-layer model. We used a neural network algorithm to build the second-layer model to enhance the predictive model fit. Moreover, we used the particle swarm optimization algorithm to optimize the crucial parameters involved in the model. Extensive numerical experiments were conducted on carbon trading data from the Beijing carbon trading market in the past five years (2016-2021), and showed that our proposed method is superior to other popular methods such as LightGBM, support vector machine, and k-nearest neighbor.
AB  - 一些国家为应对全球变暖制定了碳中和计划，也由此衍生出各种碳交易市场。参与碳交易的各方都希望从中获得最大利益，这就要求参与者准确判断碳交易价格。因此，本研究提出了一种预测碳交易价格的两阶段异质集合方法。为了准确把握时间序列数据的特征，我们根据滞后长度法、移动平均法、变模分解法和经验模分解法提取了四个特征集。随后，线性回归、神经网络、随机森林和 XGBoost 四种算法构建了第一层模型。我们使用神经网络算法构建第二层模型，以增强预测模型的拟合度。此外，我们还使用了粒子群优化算法来优化模型中的关键参数。我们在过去五年（2016-2021 年）北京碳交易市场的碳交易数据上进行了广泛的数值实验，结果表明，我们提出的方法优于 LightGBM、支持向量机和 k-nearest neighbor 等其他流行方法。
