AB  - A transition to a low carbon future will include a medium-to-long run period in which intermittent renewables co-exist with conventional fossil fuel electricity generators. Fossil fuel generators have frequent startups and shut-downs during the transition. A dynamic competition model is developed that allows for costly cycling of conventional generators. We analyze long run effects of renewable subsidies and carbon prices in the Electric Reli-ability Council of Texas system using the dynamic model. Accounting for costly generator cycling leads to large changes in equilibrium outcomes and changes policy predictions. The dynamic model predicts higher subsidies or carbon taxes are required to achieve CO2 re-duction targets compared to a static model without costly generator cycling. The dynamic model predicts the cost of CO2 reduction is 40 -80% greater than the static model pre-diction. The dynamic model predicts a much larger gap between CO2 reduction costs for carbon taxes and renewable subsidies; $303 million/year, compared to a static model pre-diction of $209 million/year.(c) 2023 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.
AB  - 向低碳未来的过渡将包括一个中长期的运行期，在此期间，间歇性可再生能源与传统的化石燃料发电机并存。 在过渡期间，化石燃料发电机会频繁启动和关闭。 我们建立了一个动态竞争模型，允许传统发电机进行高成本的循环。 我们利用该动态模型分析了德克萨斯州电力可靠性委员会系统中可再生能源补贴和碳价格的长期影响。 考虑到代价高昂的发电机循环会导致均衡结果发生巨大变化，并改变政策预测。 与不考虑高成本发电机循环的静态模型相比，动态模型预测实现二氧化碳减排目标需要更高的补贴或碳税。 动态模型预测的二氧化碳减排成本比静态模型预测的成本高 40 - 80%。 动态模型预测碳税和可再生补贴的二氧化碳减排成本差距更大；为 3.03 亿美元/年，而静态模型的预测值为 2.09 亿美元/年。 保留所有权利。
