AB  - This paper provides novel estimates of the implicit cost of carbon abatement associated with the COVID-19 crisis. We compare that to the costs from renewable investments that would lead to similar abatement. Focusing on the Spanish economy and its power sector, we combine machine learning and simulation tools to construct a precise counterfactual of market performance in absence of the crisis. Results suggest that power sector CO2 emissions fell by 4.13 Million Tons (about 11.5%) during 2020 due to the pandemic, less than half of the actual year-on-year emissions reductions. Investing in renewables to achieve similar carbon abatement would yield an implicit cost of 60-65 Euro/Ton of CO2. Conversely, the pandemic caused a substantial GDP loss in Spain, relative to the extent of overall carbon abatement. The resulting cost of carbon abatement associated with the pandemic thus exceeded 7 thousand Euro/Ton.
AB  - 本文对与 COVID-19 危机相关的碳减排隐含成本进行了新的估算。 我们将其与可再生能源投资的成本进行了比较，后者将带来类似的减排效果。 我们以西班牙经济及其电力行业为重点，结合机器学习和模拟工具，构建了在没有危机的情况下市场表现的精确反事实。 结果表明，由于大流行病的影响，2020 年电力行业的二氧化碳排放量减少了 413 万吨（约 11.5%），不到实际同比减排量的一半。 投资可再生能源以实现类似的碳减排效果，其隐含成本为每吨二氧化碳 60-65 欧元。 相反，相对于整体碳减排量而言，大流行病给西班牙造成了巨大的国内生产总值损失。 因此，与大流行病相关的碳减排成本超过 7000 欧元/吨。
