AB  - While the technical feasibility of power systems based on renewables has been established, there are concerns that a system with high shares of variable renewable electricity cannot be achieved through an energy-only market. At the root of these concerns is the merit order effect, which describes the price-depressing effect stemming from the deployment of wind and solar. More broadly speaking, this would imply a discrepancy between the way least-cost planning models select investments, and what investments are profitable in the energy-only market. The two perspectives align, however, quite well if meaningful pricing mechanisms for carbon emissions and involuntary load shedding are implemented. While meaningful carbon prices are largely sufficient to decarbonize the power system, achieving supply security through scarcity pricing requires careful market design, which fosters demand participation and storage investment, due to the threat of supply and price volatility. Both reduce volatility and induce a range of new price signals. These smooth out the price duration curve and, in turn, reduce risk in generation investments through more predictable prices.
AB  - 虽然以可再生能源为基础的电力系统在技术上是可行的，但也有人担心通过纯能源市场无法实现可再生能源电力占比高的系统。 这些担忧的根源在于绩序效应，它描述了风能和太阳能部署所产生的压低价格效应。 更广义地说，这意味着最低成本规划模型选择投资的方式与纯能源市场中哪些投资有利可图之间存在差异。 然而，如果对碳排放和非自愿负荷削减实施有意义的定价机制，这两种观点就会非常一致。 有意义的碳价格在很大程度上足以实现电力系统的去碳化，而通过稀缺性定价实现供应安全则需要精心的市场设计，由于供应和价格波动的威胁，这将促进需求参与和储能投资。 这两者都能减少波动，并诱发一系列新的价格信号。 这将使价格持续时间曲线更加平滑，进而通过更可预测的价格降低发电投资的风险。
