AB  - Companies are increasingly relying on emission reductions attributable to their adoption of renewable electricity to achieve net-zero emission targets. However, there is a risk of double counting of emission reductions threatening the credibility of corporate climate actions due to defective accounting rules of GHG emissions related to electricity consumption and the overlap between different market-based instruments, including carbon credit markets, renewable power purchase agreements, and renewable energy certificates. Using data of 63 major Chinese companies in seven sectors, we quantitatively assess the risks of double counting related to corporate sourcing of renewables and their consequent influences on the alignment of corporate emission trajectories with the 1.5 degrees C goal of the Paris Agreement. Results show that 7.1% of the electricity consumed by sample companies in 2021 was from renewable energy procurement and deployment, with which they reported 8.27 Mt of CO(2)e emission reductions compared to the scenario with no renewable electricity consumption. However, emission reductions that could be double counted are predicted to be 0.9-1.3 times as many as emission reductions that companies will report during 2021-2030. After adjustment of the reported emissions that might be underestimated due to double counting, the overall emission trajectories of sample companies are no longer aligned with the 1.5 degrees C goal. Our findings suggest that it is urgently needed to improve the corporate carbon accounting rules and increase the transparency of corporate carbon disclosures.
AB  - 企业越来越多地依靠采用可再生能源发电所带来的减排量来实现净零排放目标。 然而，由于与电力消费相关的温室气体排放核算规则存在缺陷，以及碳信用市场、可再生能源电力购买协议和可再生能源证书等不同市场工具之间存在重叠，减排量存在重复计算的风险，威胁着企业气候行动的可信度。 我们利用七个行业中 63 家中国主要企业的数据，定量评估了与企业可再生能源来源相关的重复计算风险及其对企业排放轨迹与《巴黎协定》1.5 摄氏度目标一致性的影响。 结果显示，2021 年样本公司 7.1% 的电力消耗来自可再生能源的采购和部署，与没有可再生能源电力消耗的情景相比，样本公司报告的 CO(2)e 减排量为 827 万吨。 然而，据预测，可能被重复计算的减排量是企业在 2021-2030 年期间报告减排量的 0.9-1.3 倍。 在对可能因重复计算而被低估的报告排放量进行调整后，样本公司的总体排放轨迹不再与 1.5 摄氏度的目标一致。 我们的研究结果表明，迫切需要改进企业碳会计规则，提高企业碳信息披露的透明度。
