AB  - Mobilising the work of Alfred Schutz, this paper argues that action is inherently projection, and seeks to understand how calculation becomes entangled in action as projection and projects. We pursue this aim through an empirical study of the birth of an in-vitro carbon market in Australia. We demonstrate how, prior to its birth, the market was projected by means of two complementary activities - (1) the anticipatory visualization of a completed market through multiple means including texts, numbers, and economic models, and (2) operational infrastructuring through boundary-work, standardization, and the public design of devices to help manage the politics of projection. Calculation penetrates both processes, although different calculations were made. Through theorising action as projection, we highlight the temporal hybridity of action - how past, present, and future are encapsulated in calculative action, and why futures are not terra nova but familiar spaces, made with relatable knowledge of the past and present.
AB  - 本文以阿尔弗雷德-舒茨的研究为基础，认为行动本质上就是投射，并试图理解计算是如何与作为投射和项目的行动纠缠在一起的。 为了实现这一目标，我们对澳大利亚体外碳市场的诞生进行了实证研究。 我们展示了在该市场诞生之前，是如何通过两种互补活动对其进行预测的--(1) 通过文本、数字和经济模型等多种手段，对一个完整市场的预期可视化；(2) 通过边界工作、标准化和公共设备设计，对运行基础设施进行重组，以帮助管理预测政治。 计算渗透到这两个过程中，尽管所做的计算有所不同。 通过将行动理论化为投射，我们强调了行动的时间混合性--过去、现在和未来如何被囊括在计算行动中，以及为什么未来不是新大陆，而是熟悉的空间，是用过去和现在的相关知识创造出来的。
