AB  - The energy mix transition has accelerated the need for more accurate emissions reporting throughout the petroleum supply chain. Despite increasing environmental regulations and pressure for emissions disclosure, the low resolution of existing carbon footprint assessment does not account for the complexity of crude oil trading. The lack of source crude traceability has led to poor visibility into the "well-to-refinery-entrance" carbon intensities at the level of granular pathways between producers and destination markets. Using high-fidelity datasets, optimization algorithms to facilitate supply chain traceability and bottom-up, physics-based emission estimators, we show that the variability in global "well-to-refinery-entrance" carbon intensities at the level of crude trade pathways is significant: 4.2-214.1 kg-CO2-equivalent/barrel with a volume-weighted average of 50.5 kg-CO2-equivalent/barrel. Coupled with oil supply forecasts under 1.5 degrees C scenarios up to 2050, this variability translates to additional CO2-equivalent savings of 1.5-6.1 Gigatons that could be realized solely by prioritizing low-carbon supply chain pathways without other capital-intensive mitigation measures.
AB  - 能源结构转型加快了整个石油供应链对更准确的排放报告的需求。 尽管环保法规和排放披露的压力不断增加，但现有碳足迹评估的分辨率较低，无法解释原油交易的复杂性。 由于缺乏原油来源的可追溯性，在生产商和目的地市场之间的细粒度路径层面上，"从炼油厂到入口 "碳强度的可视性很差。 利用高保真数据集、促进供应链可追溯性的优化算法以及自下而上、基于物理学的排放估算器，我们表明，在原油贸易路径层面，全球 "从炼油厂到入口 "的碳强度变化很大： 4.2-214.1 千克-CO2 当量/桶，体积加权平均值为 50.5 千克-CO2 当量/桶。 再加上到 2050 年摄氏 1.5 度情景下的石油供应预测，这一变化相当于额外节省了 1.5-6.1 千兆吨的二氧化碳当量，而这仅仅可以通过优先考虑低碳供应链途径来实现，而无需采取其他资本密集型减缓措施。
